soffico.customerapi.channel

Class ChannelInboundAdapter

  • java.lang.Object
    • soffico.customerapi.channel.ChannelInboundAdapter
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    emds.epi.decl.server.communicationengine.ChannelInstance, emds.epi.decl.server.communicationengine.InboundChannel

    public abstract class ChannelInboundAdapter
extends java.lang.Object
implements emds.epi.decl.server.communicationengine.InboundChannel
    Base class for a user defined inbound channels. As an implementor, one has to derive the own channel class from this base class. Please see the example channel how it will be used

      • submitAsynchronousMessage

        public void submitAsynchronousMessage(OrchestraTransaction transaction,
                                      java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object> inboundParameter)
                               throws OrchestraCustomerException
        Fire an received message to the underlying orchestra subsystems. The message will be catched and processed by an process modell that is capable of receiving such events. When the message was sent, the control flow proceeds without waiting for the completion of the underlying process.
